history.content:
No, because you can't be enrolled in one part of the class but not the other.

Like in the old system, I don't think you can check your waitlist position for your discussion. But you can look at the number of people on the waitlist for your discussion to get a sense, assuming you just enrolled.

I am a junior in EECS and I'm trying to enroll in CS 161. The discussion I chose has open seats, but when I enroll in the class, it says I am waitlisted for both the discussion and lecture. If there are open seats in the discussion, shouldn't I be enrolled for the discussion section and only be on the waitlist for the lecture? Also, the discussion does not say the waitlist position number, there is only a number for the lecture.
